needs a little help, then it would seem perfectly natural for him
to seek out another sportswriter. That, apparently, is what Walter
Matthau did. Oddly enough, Matthau, the Tony-award and Academy
Award-winning actor, might be, as Oscar Madison, the most famous
sportswriter of his time, Red Smith, Jimmy Cannon, Jim Murray and
