<P>
   GRAHAM-DANCE-COMPANY (New York) _ Things looked bleak for the
virtually bankrupt Martha Graham dance company six weeks ago when
it canceled its performances for the year and closed down its
school. Now they look bleaker. The board changed locks on the
warehouse where it keeps costumes fearing that Ron Protas, its
former artistic director, would take them. Protas, whom Graham
herself chose, is working to prevent the company from performing
any of Graham's dances. Many of the troupe's 17 members have been
discussing whether to organize a boycott of the dances, and Protas
is talking of establishing a new company. The wrestling match at
times takes on aspects of an opera bouffe, but for many too much is
at stake for any laughter. By Doreen Carvajal.
