<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Friday, July 7, 2000 are moving today
to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-MEXICO _ Upcoming meetings between newly elected
Mexican president Vicente Fox and Clinton, Gore and Bush will
provid excellent opportunities to revisit two countries' migrant
labor policies _ with a view to expanding guest worker programs.
Georgia, with 300,000 Mexican workers here, has a big stake in
this. (Atlanta Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-ROADS _ You may be able to get away from traffic, but
even in the Chattahoochee National Forest today , you can't get
away from roads. On three -fourths of the 749,454 acres of forest,
no matter where you hike, fish or birdwatch, you're within a half
mile of a road. The Chattahoochee has lost 79,000 acres of roadless
area in the last 20 years. (Atlanta Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   ERNIEMURRAY-COLUMN_ Check and see if you're missing a beagle. If
so, I think I may have yours, ticks and all.(EMurray, Lufkin Daily
News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ Otto, the 13-pound street tomcat who adopted me
three years ago, and Kiki, the 5-pound Siamese step-cat who regards
me as the evil step-owner, are confirmed homebodies. I can predict
almost to the minute where you will find either of these cats at
any given time.(Borders, Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ David Ruiz is a career armed robber who first
ran afoul of the law at 16. Ruiz is no candidate for citizen of the
year. Nonetheless, Ruiz, a native Austinite, distinguished himself
by being the lead plaintiff in the longest-running prison reform
lawsuit in the nation. As a result of that suit, the courts ruled
that even convicts have fundamental rights. (Garcia, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
