<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ARMANI-SLEEK-FAIRCHILD-ART-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SLEEK CHIC  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by clients of ``HIGH STYLE AND MORE.''
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 (Three color slides) 
 From W magazine 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    Giorgio Armani is justly celebrated for his sleek, feminine and
sophisticated style. He got Hollywood hooked on Armani, and many
loyalists, such as Michelle Pfeiffer and Jodie Foster, wear his
clothes around the clock.
 &HT;    So it isn't surprising that, in a season when accessories are in
the forefront of fashion, the designer is relaunching a terrific
collection of handbags, shoes and small leather goods.
 &HT;    ``It's a very exciting time in fashion, and accessories are a
part of that,'' Armani says. ``People are looking for ways to make
a fashion statement, not a loud, in-your-face statement, but one
that suggests their personalities and styles. Accessories are
decorative. They enhance a wardrobe, but they never become the
wardrobe.''
 &HT;    The collection consists of cleanlined pieces, many in vibrant
shades and exotic skins.
 &HT;    ``Color is wonderful,'' the designer says. ``And exotic skins
add texture and patterns, making beautiful accents for my
clothes.''
 &HT;    According to Judith Collinson, executive vice-president of
Barneys New York, ``This line is very cohesive. There is a creative
energy throughout. There's also a retro feeling to some of the
handbag designs, which is new.''
 &HT;    The looks, which Kal Ruttenstein, senior vice-president for
fashion direction at Bloomingdale's, describes as ``strong, sexy,
up-to-date and exciting,'' range from elongated python clutches in
wild colors like fuchsia and orange to bare stiletto lizard sandals
in a pale mint hue.
 &HT;    There are also more ladylike offerings: small structured
top-handle bags in ostrich and alligator or lizard mid-heel pumps,
along with colored beaded handbags and shoes for evening that
perfectly complement the designer's drop-dead eveningwear.
 c.2000 Fairchild Publications 
<TEXT>
