J.C. Watts, R-Okla., for key roles at the Republican National
Convention. Naming a Hispanic, a woman and a black to the posts
underscores Texas Gov. Bush's effort to reach out to ethnic
minorities and bridge the gender gap in this presidential campaign
against Vice President Al Gore. By GARY MARTIN.
