</P>
<P>
   STRIPERS (Chatham, Mass.) _ When the striper hit my little sand
eel imitation about 15 yards out, right at the edge of the channel,
it felt like I'd gotten stuck on a log. Except there are no logs on
the vast and sandy bottoms that comprise the shallow Monomoy flats
just south of Chatham on Cape Cod. Then this particular log decided
to head for Nantucket with a burst of energy and speed that caught
me off guard. By FRED LeBRUN.
</P>
