   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ The New York Times just
discovered that California is no longer predominantly white, or as
the Times put it, ``the California of postwar popular imagination,
of the Beach Boys and the John Birch Society, of Disneyland and
monochromatic Pleasantvilles.'' Ah yes, remember the days when
everyone in California was blond, even Annette Funicello. By ROB
MORSE.
</P>
