   To kill food-poisoning bacteria when grilling:
</P>
<P>
   --Cook meat, poultry and fish thoroughly until well done, and
serve hot.
</P>
<P>
   --Never consume raw meat.
</P>
<P>
   --Reheat cooked food until very hot _ about 165 degrees
Fahrenheit.
</P>
<P>
   --Refrigerate, or store in an ice chest, uncooked chicken in
plastic food storage bags or containers until ready for cooking or
marinating.
</P>
<P>
   --Store food containing eggs, poultry, meat or dairy products
separately to avoid cross contamination.
