   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CHECHNYA _ SHATILI, Republic of Georgia _ Destroying the
credibility of Russian generals who repeatedly issue statements
that the war in Chechnya is over, Chechen rebel leaders have
launched a new round of deadly attacks on the Russian army.
Throughout the 10-month-old war, the rebels have evaded Russian
attacks by holing up in secretive headquarters in the snow-capped
Caucausus mountains and escaping over the porous border with
Georgia. New evidence shows that rebels are taking refuge in
Georgia, while the Kremlin has undertaken a handful of incursions
into Georgian territory itself, threatening to turn what Moscow has
called a ``domestic conflict'' into a regional one. (Coker, Cox
News Service)
</P>
