<P>
   BUSH-HISPANICS (Austin, Texas) _ In press conference noting
George W. Bush's 54th birthday, members of an organization of
Hispanic Democrats send him two birthday wishes _ removal of Reyn
Archer as Texas' state health director and support for confirmation
of Enrique Moreno to a federal appeals court. The group also gives
the Republican presidential hopeful bus fare to visit rural housing
developments for the poor. By JULIE MASON.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-MEDICARE (Chicago) _ Vice President Al Gore says he would
do more as president to protect and expand Medicare than Republican
George W. Bush would. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   CONVENTIONS-PROTEST (Washington) _ Leaders of protest groups
planning to rally thousands at the Republican and Democratic
National Conventions promise ``massive civil disobedience'' in
Philadelphia and Los Angeles. Both nominating sessions are expected
to attract demonstrators who advocate environmental, civil rights
and anti-corporate causes. By MARK HELM.
</P>
