   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   INDIAN-LAND (Undated) _ The Alabama-Coushatta Indian tribe has
prevailed in a 17-year legal fight with the federal government over
ownership rights to 2.85 million acres of East Texas pine forest.
Similar claims with some 20 tribes have been settled around the
nation. By JAMES KIMBERLY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS-PAINT (Houston) _ The Houston school district has sued
the nation's biggest paint companies, seeking the huge sums of
money it will take to get rid of lead paint in their schools.
Similar suits have been brought by other cities, including
Philadelphia and New York, and have failed. By BILL MURPHY.
</P>
