   MIDEAST-TALKS-ASSESS (Jerusalem) _ There is a go-for-broke
quality to the Israeli and American approach to the coming Camp
David summit meeting, which starts Tuesday with the stated goal of
ending a 52-year-old blood-steeped conflict. But for the
Palestinians, whose participation is more reluctant, there is at
best an aspiration that the three-way meeting will serve as a
stop-gap measure to keep alive the stalemated peace process so that
a partial deal can be achieved by September. A news analysis by
Deborah Sontag. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news
