<HEADER>
A4868 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      07-06 0160
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Friday, July 7, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Gerry Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   DNC-PROTEST (Los Angeles) _ Leaders of a protest coalition say
they plan to hold demonstrations in many areas of downtown Los
Angeles during the Democratic National Convention and they won't
stay within designated protest areas. By Bill Hillburg. (Will move
in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   JURORS-PAY (Los Angeles) _ For years, California residents have
griped about the $5-a-day they are paid for jury duty. Starting
this month they will get $15 a day but only on the second day of
jury service -- the first day is still just $5. By Jason Kandel.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and the ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
