<HEADLINE>
SITE OF THE WEEK
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVID BLOOM 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CultureFinder.com: A nifty place to find high ``kulcha'' in
1,500 cities around the country, in classical music, opera, theater
and art. &QL; 
Where: www.culturefinder.com &QL; 
What's cool: The search function is terrific, allowing you to
search by artist or arts organization, date, venue or city, with
listings from 3,000 arts organizations. It boasts more than 300,000
event listings, with quick links to descriptions of each event,
phone numbers and addresses, even the ability to buy tickets for
many events online. &QL; 
Features: Background information on classical musicians, opera,
theater, art; special sections on Broadway shows and gossip; a
spotlight on ``travel-worthy'' events; a free e-mail newsletter
spotlighting the coming week's notable events; even a link to
Moviefone.com for film listings and tickets. &QL; 
You'll like this if: Your idea of pop culture is Andy Warhol and
Roy Lichtenstein instead of Britney Spears and 'N Sync. &QL;
