<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Ramseys downsizing to pay debts, lawyer says
 &HT;    By Craig Schneider
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ John and Patsy Ramsey are gearing down their lavish
lifestyle to pay off legal debts, selling their $700,000 Atlanta
home and living in a rented apartment here, their attorney said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think they're on skid row, but this represents a
drastically different lifestyle,'' Atlanta lawyer Lin Wood said.
``They are in a lot of debt, and it's costing them their home in
Atlanta.''
</P>
<P>
   Wood did not disclose the Ramseys' level of debt or how much
they would be asking for the house purchased in 1997 on Paces Ferry
Road in northwest Atlanta. ``I can only tell you that their legal
fees and expenses were massive,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The Ramseys plan on remaining in Atlanta, where their son,
Burke, attends a private school and where both John and Patsy have
relatives, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Wood also confirmed that the Ramseys have bought a
1,300-square-foot vacation home in the northern Michigan resort
town of Charlevoix,where they had a larger vacation home when their
daughter JonBenet was killed.
</P>
<P>
   But he stressed that the new house is ``very modest'' with three
bedrooms and one bath. The house requires some remodeling, which he
said John Ramsey plans to do himself.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
