<P>
   (NYT2) WASHINGTON -- July 6, 2000 -- CIR-ABOUT.COM -- About.com
is a linked network of 700 Web sites. The content on each site is
created by people, who may or may not be professionals in the
fields they cover and who are not employees of About.com. Scott
Kurnit, the chief executive of About.com, addressed about 70 of the
Web site's guides at a June conference in Washington. Kurnit
founded the company in 1996 as The Mining Co., changing the name
shortly after it went public. (Susana Raab/The New York Times)
Story moved on 07/05/00
