<SLUG> BC-SHAMROCK-DISNEY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHAMROCK TO INVEST IN OPENMOBILE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHRIS SIEROTY 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BURBANK, Calif. _ Shamrock Holdings of California Inc., the
investment company of the Roy E. Disney family, is teaming up with
a German venture capital firm to invest $11 million in OpenMobile
Corp., a company official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Clifford A. Miller, a managing partner with Burbank-based
Shamrock Holdings, said the decision to join forces with Wellington
Partners was part of the company's overall investment strategy.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are focused on a number of investment objectives in Europe
and Israel,'' Miller said. ``The executives running this company
(OpenMobile) are very experienced. It gave us a strong comfort
level to go into business with them.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller declined to disclose the company's share of the
transaction.
</P>
<P>
   Shamrock Holdings was founded in 1978 by Roy Disney, son of Roy
E. Disney and nephew of Walt Disney, and Stanley Gold, he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are focused on backing real technologies alongside quality
management teams and investment partners,'' added Gold, Shamrock's
president and chief executive officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our concept is to leverage Shamrock's global expertise and
relationships to improve our portfolio companies' opportunities for
success,'' Gold said.
</P>
<P>
   OpenMobile, a Scandinavian-based company, is in the process of
building a global platform for mobile services for wireless
operators and content developers.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to its presence in Europe, OpenMobile, a newly
registered U.S. company, plans to begin operations in the United
States and Asia later this year.
</P>
<P>
   The chief operating officer of OpenMobile is Pekka Palin,
co-founder and former CEO of Wapit Ltd., Europe's leading developer
of mobile services.
</P>
<P>
   ``OpenMobile's management has a proven track record in the
wireless space,'' said Robert Moskowitz, who represents Shamrock on
the OpenMobile board, in a statement. ``In a world of great ideas
and technologies, the ability to implement and deliver remains the
key competitive advantage.''
</P>
